history.content: I'm in 126 this semester and its a great class, and I would recommend that you take it. The beginning is very difficult for students like myself whose only background to this class was cs70, but after it has gotten more manageable. I would estimate that I put in ~25 hrs a week into this class, so it is definitely time consuming, but it is still very important and you'll definitely get much more out of it than 140.

children.subject: Interesting, I thought cs70 was sufficient preparation for ee 126. The first 1/3 of the course is largely a rehash of CS 70 probability (although the problems are harder). I'd suggest making sure that your knowledge of cs70 probability is strong to make your life easier.

history.content: Hi, I'm thinking about taking EECS126 next semester, but would like to get an idea of the workload. I would be taking 126, 61c as my only techs. I did average in CS 61AB, and 70, and I heard that the a high portion of the students in eecs126 have a significant math background, so it is much harder to get a good grade. Could any students who have tended to perform average/slightly above average in the lower divs comment on the difficulty of 126? I am considering taking Prob140 instead if the workload is too high. Thank you
